   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1816-05-06_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1816-05-06">May 06, 1816</date>
                  <lb/>
               </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p> My dear Madam, I am <choice>
                  <orig>asham<lb/>
                ed</orig>
                  <reg>ashamed</reg>
               </choice>of having kept you so long<lb/>
                in ignorance of what you<lb/>
                must be anxious to know<lb/>
                the safe arrival of the two<lb/>
                shawls -- they arrived a<lb/>
                month ago in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName> but<lb/>
                they had to travel from <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Belfast_IE">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Bel<lb/>
                    fast</orig>
                     <reg>Belfast</reg>
                  </choice>
               </placeName> to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName> &amp; from <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName>
               <lb/>
                to me - The fact is they have<lb/>
                been a month at my <choice>
                  <orig>bro<lb/>
                    ther</orig>
                  <reg>brother</reg>
               </choice>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Sneyds</orig>
                     <reg>Sneyd's</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> house in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Dub<lb/>
                        lin</orig>
                     <reg>Dublin</reg>
                  </choice>
               </placeName>and he was so much<lb/>
                in misery about the<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1816-05-06_page02.jpg"/>              
                health of his wife that he<lb/>
                would never answer this<lb/>
                simple question <quote>"Are the<lb/>
                    shawls safe at your house<lb/>
                    or not?" --</quote>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p> They have never yet blessed<lb/>
                    my eyes but <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">Sneyd</persName> who<lb/>
                    is a mighty good judge<lb/>
                    lets me know <hi rend="underline">this morning</hi>
               <lb/>
                    in these words<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <quote>
                  <hi rend="underline">"Your shawls are safe &amp;<lb/>
                    handsome"--</hi>
               </quote>--<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I now send you <del><unclear>an answered</unclear></del>
               <lb/>
               a note to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HoarF1"><unclear>Miss<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>.</unclear> Hoare</persName>
               <lb/>
                    begging them to pay to<lb/>
               <add>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">Mr. Miles</persName> must present the note himself</add>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xmlMileJ1">Mr. Miles</persName> L11 - 11 - 0 -  The<lb/>
                    amount I believe of my<lb/>
                    debt to you for the shawls<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1816-05-06_page03.jpg"/>               
                    - I think you said <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. E's</persName> was<lb/>
                    four guineas and a half<lb/>
                    and mine six guineas<lb/>
                and a half. -- but <choice>
                  <orig>unluck<lb/>
                    ily</orig>
                  <reg>unluckily</reg>
               </choice> I cannot find your<lb/>
                    letter. If I mistake let me<lb/>
                    know and I will send<lb/>
                    you the balance when I<lb/>
                    pay for the shoes - I wish<lb/>
                    you had mentioned how<lb/>
                    much I am in your debt<lb/>
                    for them? - I have been<lb/>
                    very anxious to send you<lb/>
                    the money for the shawls<lb/>
                but waited from day <choice>
                  <orig>to<lb/>
                    day</orig>
                  <reg>today</reg>
               </choice>to hear of them --<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> If you send the shoes &amp;<lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1816-05-06_page04.jpg"/>               
                    boots packed up in a brown<lb/>
                    paper parcel to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntR1" cert="medium">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Hunters</persName>
               <lb/>
                    directed to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss E</persName>- to wait<lb/>
                    till called for I think in<lb/>
                    the course of the next<lb/>
                    month a friend will<lb/>
                    call &amp; bring them over<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> -- Pray dont vex <choice>
                  <orig>your<lb/>
                self</orig>
                  <reg>yourself</reg>
               </choice>at having missed one<lb/>
                opportunity for I know<lb/>
                it was not likely they could<lb/>
                be in time for that &amp; am<lb/>
                in no hurry.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I beg you will make<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName> Miles tell you <add>honestly</add> what he<lb/>
                hears said about <title ref="./Workography.xml#Comic1">Comic <choice>
                     <orig>Dra<lb/>
                    mas</orig>
                     <reg>Dramas</reg>
                  </choice>
               </title>of mine which are just<lb/>
                    coming out - Let him call at<lb/>
              
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntW1" cert="medium">Hunters</persName>
         for a copy for you<lb/>
                    or for himself -- The same thing <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">My father</persName> has been rather<lb/>
                    better these last 3 days<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer> 
                 I am Dear Madam yours sincerely<lb/>
               <persName xml:id="EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth<lb/>
               </persName>
            </closer>
         </div>
